\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 What is the Extended Key Usage Extension?
\b0 \
The Extended Key Usage Extension (EKU) is much like the Key Usage Extension (KUE), except that EKU values are defined in terms of \'93purpose\'94 (for example, signing OCSP responses, identifying an SSL client and so on), and are easily extensible.\'a0 EKU is defined with object identifiers called OIDs.\'a0
\f1  If the EKU extension is omitted, all operations are potentially valid.
